## WBS maintenance rule

`docs/project-management/wbs.md` is the source of truth for task breakdown.

- Any task that creates/deletes/renames/splits/merges/re-scopes/completes a feature
  must check whether the WBS is affected and update it in the same commit.
- If the WBS is unaffected, the final report must state: `WBS update: not needed — <reason>`.

### Commit traceability rule (mandatory)

Every commit that creates, advances, or completes a WBS work package MUST append a
line to the **Commit Traceability Log (§10 of `docs/project-management/wbs.md`)** in
the SAME commit: short commit id, date, WBS ID(s) touched, one-line summary.
Append-only, newest first.

