## Path convention for cross-references (canonical)

Whenever a markdown file references another file inside backticks, the path MUST be
**repo-root absolute, no leading slash**:

```
✓  `docs/business/<feature>/<spec>.md`     ✓  `CLAUDE.md`
✗  /docs/...   ✗  ../docs/...   ✗  bare-filename.md
```

`doc_guard` enforces this. An agent finding a non-conforming ref MUST fix it in the
same commit and report it under "Drift detected".

