## Hard rules (violation = task fail)

- Do NOT commit code without running the Pre-commit parity check.
- Do NOT implement from assumption when docs already define a contract.
- Do NOT edit generated files <!-- FILL: list generated-file globs, e.g. `*.g.dart`, `dist/**` -->.
- Do NOT hardcode route strings, colors, text styles, durations, or user-facing strings — use the project's tokens/constants.
- Do NOT change schema/persistence without a migration, schema docs, migration docs, and tests in the SAME commit.
- Do NOT mark a docs item from Specified/Target/Future to Implemented unless code truly implements it AND a test verifies it.
- Do NOT keep persistent data only in memory / provider state.
- Do NOT bypass the UseCase → Repository → DataSource flow.
- Do NOT violate dependency direction: domain imports nothing outward; presentation never imports data directly. Dependencies point inward.
- Do NOT add a route without updating route constants AND `docs/business/navigation/navigation-flow.md` in the same commit.
- Do NOT leave docs referencing an old term/route/field after a rename.
- Do NOT mark a task "done" before the Pre-commit parity check passes.
- Do NOT run verification commands ad hoc — everything goes through `node tool/verify/run.mjs`. Ad-hoc runs write no marker, so the pre-commit hook blocks the commit.
