## Auto-delegation (subagent fan-out)

After a **code-changing** task and once `node tool/verify/run.mjs` PASSes, **before
the final report**, fan out **in parallel** (one turn, multiple Agent calls):

- `code-reviewer` — review the working-tree diff across correctness, architecture, doc-parity, and project gates.
- `docs-drift-detector` — sweep for remaining doc-code drift (stale path/symbol refs, WBS gaps).

Review the **working-tree diff**, do NOT commit first. In the fan-out prompt instruct
each reviewer to run `git add -N . && git diff`. Fix blocker findings before finishing;
list minor findings in the report for the user to decide.

Skip the fan-out (and say why) when: docs-only task, trivial rename/format, the user
asked for speed / "no review", or verify has not passed yet.

