## Verification (single entry)

```
node tool/verify/run.mjs --quick   # inner dev loop: fast, NO marker
node tool/verify/run.mjs --docs    # docs-only change → writes marker
node tool/verify/run.mjs --code    # code change → writes marker
node tool/verify/run.mjs           # auto-detect scope
```

Command chains live in `scaffold.config.json` → `verify.docs` / `verify.code`. A PASS
writes `tool/verify/.last-pass.json` bound to the tree state; the pre-commit hook
(`--check-marker`) refuses commits without a matching marker. Edit a file after PASS →
the marker is stale → re-run.

---

## When in doubt

- Prefer a minimal, structurally correct change over a broad refactor.
- Prefer an over-cautious doc update over skipping the parity check.
- If a task requires violating any hard rule, STOP and confirm with the user first.
- If you detect doc drift the task did not ask you to fix, still report it.
